The paper deals with channel coding over Gaussian ISI channels, which is a topic in information theory and communication systems (cs.IT, cs.COMM). The focus is on the problem of mismatched decoding, which is a common issue in practical communication systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses achievable rates based on ensembles of codewords, which is a technique used in statistical inference and machine learning (cs.SI). Finally, the paper compares its results with universal decoders, which is a topic in machine learning and data compression (cs.LG).
